# Authoring Theia Extensions

## Overview

This comprehensive guide walks developers through creating and deploying Theia extensions. The documentation uses a practical "Say hello" example that adds a menu item displaying a notification.

## Prerequisites

Before beginning, developers should review the [Theia repository prerequisites](https://github.com/eclipse-theia/theia/blob/master/doc/Developing.md#prerequisites) and familiarize themselves with [creating Theia applications](/docs/composing_applications/).

## Project Layout

The recommended approach involves using the [Yeoman Generator](https://github.com/eclipse-theia/generator-theia-extension) to scaffold a Theia project with an example extension structure.

## Custom Theia Extension Structure

### Package Configuration

The extension's `package.json` serves as the foundation:

```json
{
  "name": "hello-world",
  "keywords": [
    "theia-extension"
  ],
  "version": "0.0.0",
  "files": [
    "lib",
    "src"
  ],
  "dependencies": {
    "@theia/core": "latest"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "rimraf": "latest",
    "typescript": "~5.4.5"
  },
  "scripts": {
    "prepare": "yarn run clean && yarn run build",
    "clean": "rimraf lib",
    "build": "tsc",
    "watch": "tsc -w"
  },
  "theiaExtensions": [
    {
      "frontend": "lib/browser/hello-world-frontend-module"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Key Concepts

The `theia-extension` keyword identifies packages as Theia extensions for automated discovery. Extensions wire functionality through [dependency injection](/docs/services_and_contributions#dependency-injection-di), binding implementations to contribution interfaces.

The `theiaExtensions` property specifies JavaScript modules exporting InversifyJS `ContainerModule` definitions. Extensions can contribute to frontend (UI features) or backend (language servers) components.

### Dependency Injection Module

```javascript
export default new ContainerModule(bind => {
    // add your contribution bindings here
    bind(CommandContribution).to(HelloWorldCommandContribution);
    bind(MenuContribution).to(HelloWorldMenuContribution);
});
```

### Command Implementation

Commands are data structures with ID and label; handlers implement their behavior:

```javascript
export const HelloWorldCommand = {
    id: 'HelloWorld.command',
    label: "Shows a message"
};

@injectable()
export class HelloWorldCommandContribution implements CommandContribution {

    constructor(
        @inject(MessageService) private readonly messageService: MessageService,
    ) { }

    registerCommands(registry: CommandRegistry): void {
        registry.registerCommand(HelloWorldCommand, {
            execute: () => this.messageService.info('Hello World!')
        });
    }
}
```

The `@inject` decorator provides dependencies through the container, eliminating concerns about lifecycle or source.

### Menu Integration

Making commands accessible through the UI requires implementing `MenuContribution`:

```javascript
@injectable()
export class HelloWorldMenuContribution implements MenuContribution {

    registerMenus(menus: MenuModelRegistry): void {
        menus.registerMenuAction(CommonMenus.EDIT_FIND, {
                commandId: HelloWorldCommand.id,
                label: 'Say Hello'
            });
    }
}
```

## Adding Extensions to Applications

Include extensions as dependencies in the application's `package.json`:

```json
{
  "private": true,
  "name": "browser-app",
  "version": "0.0.0",
  "dependencies": {
    "@theia/core": "latest",
    "hello-world": "0.0.0"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@theia/cli": "latest"
  },
  "scripts": {
    "bundle": "yarn rebuild && theia build --mode development",
    "rebuild": "theia rebuild:browser --cacheRoot ..",
    "start": "theia start",
    "watch": "yarn rebuild && theia build --watch --mode development"
  },
  "theia": {
    "target": "browser"
  }
}
```

## Deployment Options

Two primary deployment strategies exist:

1. **Monorepo approach**: Include the extension within a repository containing a Theia-based application that imports it
2. **NPM publishing**: Publish the extension via `yarn publish` and consume it as a dependency in applications

Additional details appear in documentation covering browser application execution and Electron deployment.

## Additional Resources

Theia provides extensive contribution interfaces (marked with `*Contribution` naming) enabling extensions to integrate with various application aspects. The "Platform Concepts & APIs" documentation section explores available interfaces and services for extending functionality.